		<div class="comment-content">
			<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/fd91265e84931489c6ced077ea828506?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-32' height='32' width='32' />			<p>Thank you for this great post.</p>
<p>Here is something you might find mildly interesting. A month ago TopCoder organized a marathon (i.e., one week long) match in which people had to write a program that reconstructs a 100&#215;100 grid of `densities&#8217; based on the information gathered from 10000 (noisy) measurements. A few tried the Radon transform but none used it in the end because it was hard to implement and didn&#8217;t work well at all with so few measurements. I wonder if people would have done better if they would have known about compressed sensing and read some of the articles you link to here&#8230;</p>

