<p>I think you might be right that the approach of developing a (fast) algorithm that can verify the RIP would be the most promising.  In particular, at the very least it would provide a quick method to justify using l1 for inverse problems in which there is known to be a sparse representation for the signal class of interest&#8230;</p>

