	<div class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 vcard parent" id="comment-41796">
		<div class="comment-metadata">
			<p class="comment-permalink"><a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2007/04/13/compressed-sensing-and-single-pixel-cameras/#comment-41796" title="Permalink to this comment">11 October, 2009 at 8:56 pm</a></p>
			<p class="comment-author"><strong class="fn">AJ</strong></p>
			 
		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-content">
			<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-32' height='32' width='32' />			<p>Professor Tao:<br />
Is there an information theoretic meaning to sparseness?</p>
<p>It seems to be that from the following two sequences the correspondence might be tricky.<br />
A=1111111111&#8230;&#8230;.<br />
B=10100100001000000001&#8230;&#8230;&#8230;.</p>
<p>It seems to me that B somehow carries more information that A even though B is sparse.</p>
<p>Thank you.</p>

<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_132742_comm_41796"></div><script type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8"><!--//--><![CDATA[//><!--
